  <intro />
  <sections>
    <section>
      <desc />
      <content>
        <p class="bodytext">The Insight Display screen enables you to view the Insight Display on the enclosure remotely. To activate the Insight Display with a device firmware less than version 2.0, click the blue <b><b>OK </b></b>button below the main display of the Insight Display. To activate the Insight Display with a device firmware of version 2.0 or greater, click the blue <b><b>OK</b></b> button next to the main display of the Insight Display. The device firmware version can be found in the Insight Display Device Information table on the Device Summary page under Enclosure Settings.</p>
        <p class="bodytext">The Insight Display renders exactly what appears on the Insight Display on the enclosure. The main menu of the Insight Display has eight selectable items: Health Summary, Enclosure Settings, Enclosure Info, Blade or Port Info, Turn Enclosure UID on, View User Note, Chat Mode, and USB Key Menu. For detailed information, see the <i>HP BladeSystem c3000 or c7000 User Guide.</i></p>
        <p class="bodytext">The tabbed pages below the Insight Display appears for all users, but the forms on these pages are only enabled for Administrators with Onboard Administrator Access permissions.</p>
        <p class="bodytext">
          <b>
            <b>Security tab</b>
          </b>
        </p>
        <p class="bodytext">This tab enables you to configure security settings on the Insight Display.</p>
        <p class="bodytext">
          <b>
            <b>Lock Buttons</b>
          </b>—Select the check box to disable button functionality on the Insight Display. This feature is only configurable from the Web interface. After entering FIPS Mode, you must set a new pin code before unlocking the LCD buttons.</p>
        <p class="bodytext">
          <b>
            <b>Enable PIN Protection</b>
          </b>—Select the check box to enable PIN code protection and to add a PIN code. This feature prevents configuration changes unless a PIN code is entered. Clear the check box to disable PIN code protection.</p>
